<br>
Especially on this server, where groups can be hard to come by, the only real perfect group is one that doesn't get you killed too fast.<br>
<br>
I'd say a healer of some type is pretty critical, as is someone who can swing a weapon (but, then, I'm an enchanter and prone to die quick without either, so I'm biased)<br>
<br>
I agree that Loot Hogs are lame, but don't agree that looting while a fight is going is the lowest of lows. Often in the groups I'm in (especially in a dungeon, like Permafrost), the corpses start to pile up, which can make it hard for me to target stuff. I'm guilty of looting while the fight is going, in other words, but I'm anything but a loot hog. Split on, fair share on merchant muck, need before greed but throw something in the pot if you win the roll (i.e. if you win a better weapon than you have, throw the one you have in and let everyone roll) has always worked for me.<br>
<br>
By the time you've got to 30, I agree you ought to have learned Human. Far as I know, hardly anyone speaks Elvish in groups anymore, but it might be all the halflings and dwarves I'm partial to hanging out with <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
Good group leaders are a bonus, but too often the leader attitude spills over into bossy buffoon, who is all to quick to order folks around and ruin the fun. I know that sounds hypocritical coming from your typically bossy enchantress, but there's a difference between someone telling the numbskull tanks when to assist (to keep us all from dying) and the bossy warrior telling me when to meditate (figured that one out about level 4 when I got the skill, thanks...)<br>
<br>
Number one criteria for me is people who aren't afraid of a little adventure. Give me a dungeon over a dreary outdoor experience grind any day.<br>
<br>
Halus<br>
31 enchantress<br>
